=== Unset produces same memo state as backdoor ===
No context (baseline):
  keyed_memo EXECUTED (run #1, memo_key=0)
  returned: result_1_key_0
With sensitive context:
  keyed_memo EXECUTED (run #2, memo_key=1)
  returned: result_2_key_1
After unset sensitive:
  returned: result_1_key_0
Via backdoor:
  returned: result_1_key_0

Total keyed_memo executions: 2

=== Agnostic set/unset doesn't affect memo key ===
With sensitive context:
  keyed_memo2 EXECUTED (run #1, memo_key=1)
  returned: result2_1_key_1
With sensitive + agnostic set:
  returned: result2_1_key_1
With sensitive + agnostic unset:
  returned: result2_1_key_1

Total keyed_memo2 executions: 1
